## Third-Party Acknowledgments

dirty-vibe builds upon and integrates with the following open-source projects:

### MCP Servers

| Project | Repository | Description |
|---------|-----------|-------------|
| **GitNexus** | [abhigyanpatwari/GitNexus](https://github.com/abhigyanpatwari/GitNexus) | Code graph and analysis MCP server (11 tools) |
| **Graphify** | [safishamsi/graphify](https://github.com/safishamsi/graphify) | Knowledge graph from meetings and documents MCP server (7 tools) |
| **Context7** | [upstash/context7](https://github.com/upstash/context7) | Library documentation MCP server (2 tools) |
| **Vibe Kanban** | [BloopAI/vibe-kanban](https://github.com/BloopAI/vibe-kanban) | Kanban board and coding agents MCP server (30 tools) |

### Storage Engines (configurable)

| Project | Repository | Description |
|---------|-----------|-------------|
| **LadybugDB** | [LadybugDB/ladybug](https://github.com/LadybugDB/ladybug) | Embedded columnar graph database |
| **FalkorDB** | [FalkorDB/FalkorDB](https://github.com/FalkorDB/FalkorDB) | High-performance graph database |
| **SQLite** | [sqlite/sqlite](https://github.com/sqlite/sqlite) | Embedded relational database (used by dirty-vibe cross-links) |

Each project is governed by its own license. Please refer to the respective
repositories for their licensing terms.
